Package: treeowen
Type: Package
Title: Efficient Game-Theoretic Explanations for Tree-Based Ensembles via Owen Values
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Hyunwook", "Koh",
    email = "hyunwook.koh@stonybrook.edu",
    role  = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides exact and Monte Carlo algorithms for computing Owen values
    in tree-based ensemble models, including gradient boosting machines
    (XGBoost, LightGBM) and random forests (Ranger). The Owen value extends the
    Shapley value to settings where features are organized into a priori groups,
    allocating attribution in two stages: first across groups, then within each
    group. The package implements hierarchy-guided group aggregation combined
    with tree-aware dynamic programming to avoid explicit outer group subset
    enumeration. Global importance measures and visualization tools (flat and
    hierarchical beeswarm plots) are also provided.
